Flank Steak with Dressing-For the Pressure Cooker

2 pounds (4 lb.) Flank steak

Dressing
3/4 cup (1 1/2 cups) Sausage meat
1 (2) Apples -- peeled & sliced
1 1/2 cups (3 cups) Dried bread crumbs
1 tablespoon (2 TBS) Onion, minced
1/4 teaspoon (1/2 tsp.) Salt
3 tablespoons (6 TBS) Fat
3/4 cup (1 cup) Water


Note: amounts given are for 1 flank steak - 4 Qt. cooker, 4 servings. Those
in parenthesis () are for 2 steaks - 6 Qt. cooker, 8 servings.
1. Heat sausage in fry pan.
2. Pour off excess fat.
3. Add the remaining stuffing ingredients, (not the fat or water).
4. Trim edges of steak.
5. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
6. Spread dressing over flank steak.
7. Roll it up loosely and tie it securely.
8. Brown steak on all sides in fat in cooker.
9. Add water.
10.Cover.